801.definition: [ἀσύνετος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G4908}}; unintelligent; by implication, wicked

802.definition: [ἀσύνθετος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G4934}}; properly, not agreed, i.e. treacherous to compacts

804.definition: [ἀσφαλής] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and sphallo (to "fail"); secure (literally or figuratively)

808.definition: [ἀσχημοσύνη] from {{G809}}; an indecency; by implication, the pudenda

809.definition: [ἀσχήμων] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G2192}} (in the sense of its congener {{G4976}}); properly, shapeless, i.e. (figuratively) inelegant

810.definition: [ἀσωτία] from a compound of {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G4982}}; properly, unsavedness, i.e. (by implication) profligacy

811.definition: [ἀσώτως] adverb from the same as {{G810}}; dissolutely

813.definition: [ἄτακτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G5021}}; unarranged, i.e. (by implication) insubordinate (religiously)

815.definition: [ἄτεκνος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5043}}; childless

816.definition: [ἀτενίζω] from a compound of {{G1}} (as a particle of union) and τείνω (to stretch); to gaze intently

817.definition: [ἄτερ] a particle probably akin to {{G427}}; aloof, i.e. apart from (literally or figuratively)

818.definition: [ἀτιμάζω] from {{G820}}; to render infamous, i.e. (by implication) contemn or maltreat

819.definition: [ἀτιμία] from {{G820}}; infamy, i.e. (subjectively) comparative indignity, (objectively) disgrace

820.definition: [ἄτιμος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5092}}; (negatively) unhonoured or (positively) dishonoured

823.definition: [ἄτομος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{G5114}}; uncut, i.e. (by implication) indivisible (an "atom" of time)

824.definition: [ἄτοπος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5117}}; out of place, i.e. (figuratively) improper, injurious, wicked

825.definition: [Ἀττάλεια] from Ἄτταλος (a king of Pergamus); Attaleia, a place in Pamphylia

827.definition: [αὐγή] of uncertain derivation; a ray of light, i.e. (by implication) radiance, dawn

828.definition: [Αὐγοῦστος] from Latin (""); Augustus, a title of the Roman emperor

829.definition: [αὐθάδης] from {{G846}} and the base of {{G2237}}; self-pleasing, i.e. arrogant

830.definition: [αὐθαίρετος] from {{G846}} and the same as {{G140}}; self-chosen, i.e. (by implication) voluntary

831.definition: [αὐθεντέω] from a compound of {{G846}} and an obsolete ἕντης (a worker); to act of oneself, i.e. (figuratively) dominate

833.definition: [αὐλή] from the same as {{G109}}; a yard (as open to the wind); by implication, a mansion

835.definition: [αὐλίζομαι] middle voice from {{G833}}; to pass the night (properly, in the open air)

836.definition: [αὐλός] from the same as {{G109}}; a flute (as blown)

837.definition: [αὐξάνω] a prolonged form of a primary verb; to grow ("wax"), i.e. enlarge (literal or figurative, active or passive)

839.definition: [αὔριον] from a derivative of the same as {{G109}} (meaning a breeze, i.e. the morning air); properly, fresh, i.e. (adverb with ellipsis of {{G2250}}) to-morrow

840.definition: [αὐστηρός] from a (presumed) derivative of the same as {{G109}} (meaning blown); rough (properly as a gale), i.e. (figuratively) severe

841.definition: [αὐτάρκεια] from {{G842}}; self-satisfaction, i.e. (abstractly) contentedness, or (concretely) a competence

843.definition: [αὐτοκατάκριτος] from {{G846}} and a derivative or {{G2632}}; self-condemned

844.definition: [αὐτόματος] from {{G846}} and the same as {{G3155}}; self-moved ("automatic"), i.e. spontaneous

845.definition: [αὐτόπτης] from {{G846}} and {{G3700}}; self-seeing, i.e. an eye-witness

846.definition: [αὐτός] from the particle αὖ (perhaps akin to the base of {{G109}} through the idea of a baffling wind) (backward); the reflexive pronoun self, used (alone or in the comparative {{G1438}}) of the third person , and (with the proper personal pronoun) of the other persons Compare {{G848}}.

847.definition: [αὐτοῦ] genitive (i.e. possessive) of {{G846}}, used as an adverb of location; properly, belonging to the same spot, i.e. in this (or that) place

848.definition: [αὑτοῦ] contracted for {{G1438}}; self (in some oblique case or reflexive relation)

849.definition: [αὐτόχειρ] from {{G846}} and {{G5495}}; self-handed, i.e. doing personally

850.definition: [αὐχμηρός] from αὐχμός (probably from a base akin to that of {{G109}}) (dust, as dried by wind); properly, dirty, i.e. (by implication) obscure

851.definition: [ἀφαιρέω] from {{G575}} and {{G138}}; to remove (literally or figuratively)

852.definition: [ἀφανής] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5316}}; non-apparent

853.definition: [ἀφανίζω] from {{G852}}; to render unapparent, i.e. (actively) consume (becloud), or (passively) disappear (be destroyed)

855.definition: [ἄφαντος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G5316}}; non-manifested, i.e. invisible

856.definition: [ἀφεδρών] from a compound of {{G575}} and the base of {{G1476}}; a place of sitting apart, i.e. a privy

857.definition: [ἀφειδία] from a compound of {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5339}}; unsparingness, i.e. austerity (asceticism)

858.definition: [ἀφελότης] from a compound of {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and φέλλος (in the sense of a stone as stubbing the foot); smoothness, i.e. (figuratively) simplicity

861.definition: [ἀφθαρσία] from {{G862}}; incorruptibility; genitive, unending existence; (figuratively) genuineness

862.definition: [ἄφθαρτος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G5351}}; undecaying (in essence or continuance)

863.definition: [ἀφίημι] from {{G575}} and ἵημι (to send; an intensive form of εἶμι, to go); to send forth, in various applications (as follow)

864.definition: [ἀφικνέομαι] from {{G575}} and the base of {{G2425}}; to go (i.e. spread) forth (by rumor)

865.definition: [ἀφιλάγαθος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5358}}; hostile to virtue

866.definition: [ἀφιλάργυρος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5366}}; unavaricious

867.definition: [ἄφιξις] from {{G864}}; properly, arrival, i.e. (by implication) departure

868.definition: [ἀφίστημι] from {{G575}} and {{G2476}}; to remove, i.e. (actively) instigate to revolt; usually (reflexively) to desist, desert, etc.

870.definition: [ἀφόβως] adverb from a compound of {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5401}}; fearlessly

873.definition: [ἀφορίζω] from {{G575}} and {{G3724}}; to set off by boundary, i.e. (figuratively) limit, exclude, appoint, etc.

874.definition: [ἀφορμή] from a compound of {{G575}} and {{G3729}}; a starting-point, i.e. (figuratively) an opportunity

875.definition: [ἀφρίζω] from {{G876}}; to froth at the mouth (in epilepsy)

876.definition: [ἀφρός] apparently a primary word; froth, i.e. slaver

878.definition: [ἄφρων] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5424}}; properly, mindless, i.e. stupid, (by implication) ignorant, (specially) egotistic, (practically) rash, or (morally) unbelieving

879.definition: [ἀφυπνόω] from a compound of {{G575}} and {{G5258}}; properly, to become awake, i.e. (by implication) to drop (off) in slumber

880.definition: [ἄφωνος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5456}}; voiceless, i.e. mute (by nature or choice); figuratively, unmeaning

881.definition: [Ἀχάζ] of Hebrew origin ({{H271}}); Achaz, an Israelite

882.definition: [Ἀχαΐα] of uncertain derivation; Achaia (i.e. Greece), a country of Europe

883.definition: [Ἀχαϊκός] from {{G882}}; an Achaian; Achaicus, a Christian

884.definition: [ἀχάριστος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{G5483}}; thankless, i.e. ungrateful

885.definition: [Ἀχείμ] probably of Hebrew origin (compare {{H3137}}); Achim, an Israelite

886.definition: [ἀχειροποίητος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5499}}; unmanufactured, i.e. inartificial

887.definition: [ἀχλύς] of uncertain derivation; dimness of sight, i.e. (probably) a cataract

888.definition: [ἀχρεῖος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{G5534}} (compare {{G5532}}); useless, i.e. (euphemistically) unmeritorious

889.definition: [ἀχρειόω] from {{G888}}; to render useless, i.e. spoil

890.definition: [ἄχρηστος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5543}}; inefficient, i.e. (by implication) detrimental

891.definition: [ἄχρι]   or ἄχρις; akin to {{G206}} (through the idea of a terminus); (of time) until or (of place) up to Compare {{G3360}}.

892.definition: [ἄχυρον] perhaps remotely from χέω (to shed forth); chaff (as diffusive)

893.definition: [ἀψευδής] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5579}}; veracious

894.definition: [ἄψινθος] of uncertain derivation; wormwood (as a type of bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) calamity)

895.definition: [ἄψυχος] from {{G1}} (as a negative particle) and {{G5590}}; lifeless, i.e. inanimate (mechanical)

896.definition: [Βάαλ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1168}}); Baal, a Phœnician deity (used as a symbol of idolatry)

897.definition: [Βαβυλών] of Hebrew origin ({{H894}}); Babylon, the capitol of Chaldæa (literally or figuratively (as a type of tyranny))

898.definition: [βαθμός] from the same as {{G899}}; a step, i.e. (figuratively) grade (of dignity)

899.definition: [βάθος] from the same as {{G901}}; profundity, i.e. (by implication) extent; (figuratively) mystery
